>Indonesian police are searching for potentially hundreds of escaped inmates following a deadly prison riot in Medan, the capital of the province of North Sumatra. At least five people died, including two guards and three prisoners.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/EabO-_iOURY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:13:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/indonesia-mass-prison-break/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Q&amp;A: What happens once the royal baby is born?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/royal-baby-qa/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/VvClDGgt9m4/index.html</link><description>Any day now, the Duchess of Cambridge is due to give birth to her first baby. What will happen once it arrives?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/VvClDGgt9m4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 12:05:42 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/royal-baby-qa/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Dementia village'' inspires new care</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Eg-e8KNd3MM/index.html</link><description>A cutting edge dementia facility -- where residents can do anything except leave and where their every move is watched by carers who also staff the village shops -- is offering a new way to deal with long term care.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Eg-e8KNd3MM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:15:02 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Raped 11-year-old stirs Chile''s abortion debate</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/1qeHYyjRlfM/index.html</link><description>Chilean President Sebastian Pinera stoked an abortion debate in his country over remarks he made about an 11-year-old girl who became pregnant after being raped by her stepfather.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/1qeHYyjRlfM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:30:32 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pope lays down law on child abuse in Vatican</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/vatican-child-abuse/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/pZZ_mCJfOUY/index.html</link><description>Pope Francis has laid down a law making it a crime to abuse children sexually or physically on Vatican grounds, the Holy See announced Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/pZZ_mCJfOUY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 10:56:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/vatican-child-abuse/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New Zealand: Prove recreational drug is safe, then you can sell</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/new-zealand-drug-law/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/TLuH2SsXZWk/index.html</link><description>The New Zealand government wants to make sure your high is safe.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/TLuH2SsXZWk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 05:08:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/new-zealand-drug-law/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>6 climb Shard to protest drilling </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/uk-greenpeace-protests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/qqJkpfp9ZW4/index.html</link><description>Six women attempted to climb one of Europe''s tallest buildings Thursday to rally against Shell''s Arctic drilling plan.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/qqJkpfp9ZW4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 21:06:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/uk-greenpeace-protests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Irish politicians debate abortion bill </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/ireland-abortion/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/uf4c5gEM_go/index.html</link><description>After hours of debate, parliamentarians in the devoutly Catholic Ireland got closer Thursday to passing a bill that would allow abortion when the mother''s life is in danger.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/uf4c5gEM_go" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 21:23:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/ireland-abortion/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Greece''s state broadcaster back</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/greece-broadcaster-on-air/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/m4Vmnzf7-OA/index.html</link><description>Greece state broadcaster ERT is back on the air after being shut down by the government in June.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/m4Vmnzf7-OA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 09:37:21 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/greece-broadcaster-on-air/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>WikiLeaks hints at Snowden ''flight''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/americas/nsa-snowden-venezuela/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/nbAJ_9-j7GQ/index.html</link><description>As speculation grows over Edward Snowden''s path to freedom, WikiLeaks teased that his "flight of liberty" campaign starts Wednesday, promising further details.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/nbAJ_9-j7GQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 08:51:23 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/americas/nsa-snowden-venezuela/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Flooding traps train passengers</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/americas/toronto-train-flooding/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/XTq6xtQxbhU/index.html</link><description>Toronto''s rush hour Monday turned into anything but -- as a deluge from a summer storm inundated the city, swamping commuters whether they traveled by rail or by road.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/XTq6xtQxbhU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:43:51 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/americas/toronto-train-flooding/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Soccer referee dismembered</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/07/world/americas/brazil-soccer-dismemberment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/xul5046QnVc/index.html</link><description>The argument started over a red card.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/xul5046QnVc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:46:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://ww