ight="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:37:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/tech/cousteau-why-im-going-to-live-in-an-underwater-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Thrill of Pamplona bull runners</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/travel/la-pamplona/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/BBUq0996AAU/index.html</link><description>More and more people risk injury each year at thrilling symbol of Spanish culture.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/BBUq0996AAU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jul 2013 07:50:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/travel/la-pamplona/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What''s in a royal name?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/europe/britain-royal-baby-name/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/5HMoOjw5KVk/index.html</link><description>Way back in the mists of time, when schoolkids were expected to learn seemingly endless lists of facts off by heart, they chanted a poem to remember the names of England''s kings and queens.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/5HMoOjw5KVk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 07:00:02 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/europe/britain-royal-baby-name/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>25 greatest engineering feats</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/travel/engineering-feats/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/cKqTK_vbDLY/index.html</link><description>The last few months have seen a fair number of impressive construction plans announced, from Norway''s intention to create the world''s first shipping tunnel, to Maldives'' plans for a space-age underwater hotel, to Dubai''s plans for the world''s biggest shopping mall.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/cKqTK_vbDLY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 10:24:28 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/travel/engineering-feats/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Rudest taxi drivers in the world?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/travel/rudest-taxi-drivers/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/b2O_NIy-eYE/index.html</link><description>Could these really be the rudest taxi drivers on the planet?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/b2O_NIy-eYE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 11:27:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/travel/rudest-taxi-drivers/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>The man who exposed Lance</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/01/sport/cycling-armstrong-doping-walsh/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/Bzihw2pXnNM/index.html</link><description>It cost his newspaper a thumping $1.6 million in legal costs as well as 13 years of his life. But journalist David Walsh was finally vindicated when Lance Armstrong confessed to doping earlier this year.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/Bzihw2pXnNM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jul 2013 21:17:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/01/sport/cycling-armstrong-doping-walsh/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Snowden to meet human rights group</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/russia-us-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/DD2X5oPnH5M/index.html</link><description>American intelligence leaker Edward Snowden is due to meet with a human rights group Friday, the press service for Moscow''s Sheremetyevo International Airport said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/DD2X5oPnH5M" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 06:37:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/russia-us-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New planet that rains glass</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/o7JqcMvJHW0/index.html</link><description>Astronomers have found a deep azure blue planet orbiting another star 63 light years away -- the first time they''ve been able to determine the actual color of a planet outside our solar system, NASA and the European Space Agency said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/o7JqcMvJHW0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 02:32:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Dementia village'' provides care</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/XD0WvdUdRCU/index.html</link><description>A cutting edge dementia facility -- where residents can do anything except leave and where their every move is watched by carers who also staff the village shops -- is offering a new way to deal with long term care.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/XD0WvdUdRCU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 21:57:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Snowden''s transit zone mysteries</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-snowden-goodman-transit/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/9W6qplys2Q8/index.html</link><description>It seemed like an exciting assignment -- go to Moscow on the trail of former NSA contractor Edward Snowden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/9W6qplys2Q8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 05:14:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-snowden-goodman-transit/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Friends, family pay tribute to slain British soldier Lee Rigby</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/uk-slain-soldier-funeral/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/kc0w8qRXdfw/index.html</link><description>Family and friends attended a military funeral Friday to pay tribute to Lee Rigby, the British soldier killed in an attack in southeast London in May.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/kc0w8qRXdfw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 07:19:52 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/uk-slain-soldier-funeral/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Irish law allows abortions if life at risk</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/ireland-abortion/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/JAC44b9bpZs/index.html</link><description>After impassioned debate, Irish lawmakers overwhelmingly passed new legislation that allows abortions if the mother''s life is at risk. The vote was 127-31 in favor of the bill.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/JAC44b9bpZs" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 06:42:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/ireland-abortion/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Karadzic genocide charge reinstated</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/netherlands-karadzic-trial/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/QBzXUtmD6yw/index.html</link><description>Former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic once again faces two genocide charges instead of one in his long-running trial over ethnic violence during the 1990s Balkan wars.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/QBzXUtmD6yw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 14:26:59 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/netherlands-karadzic-trial/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Russian court convicts whistleblower after death</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-magnitsky-convicted-posthumously/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/3uPGDEKlbqE/index.html</link><description>A whistle-blowing Russian lawyer whose death in custody strained U.S.-Russia relations was posthumously convicted in a tax case in a Moscow district court Thursday, state-run legal news agency RAPSI reported.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/3uPGDEKlbqE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 02:33:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-magnitsky-convicted-posthumously/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pope Francis lays down child sex abuse law</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/vatican-child-abuse/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/sbjH7_YYhdg/index.html</link><descrip