('http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_world.rss', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\r\n<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" media="screen" href="/~d/styles/rss2full.xsl"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" media="screen" href="http://rss.cnn.com/~d/styles/itemcontent.css"?><rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:feedburner="http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0" version="2.0">\r\n<channel>\r\n<title>CNN.com - World</title>\r\n<link>http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/index.html?eref=rss_world</link>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n<language>en-US</language>\r\n<copyright>Copyright 2013 Cable News Network LP, LLLP.</copyright>\r\n<pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 17:01:28 EDT</pubDate>\r\n<ttl>10</ttl>\r\n<image>\r\n<title>CNN.com - World</title>\r\n<link>http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/index.html?eref=rss_world</link>\r\n<url>http://i.cdn.turner.com/cnn/.e/img/1.0/logo/cnn.logo.rss.gif</url>\r\n<width>144</width>\r\n<height>33</height>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n</image>\r\n<atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_world" /><feedburner:info uri="rss/edition_world" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><item><title>Malala''s voice stronger, not silenced</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/malala-girls-education/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/zoHCj0KLjRk/index.html</link><description>The attack was meant to silence the outspoken teenager who dared to defy the Taliban''s ban against girls in school. Instead, it only made Malala''s voice more powerful. After a school year that started with a shooting, Malala now eyes a summer of speaking at the U.N., telling her story in a new book and amplifying the issue of girls education.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zoHCj0KLjRk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2013 17:03:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/malala-girls-education/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What happened to Malala''s friend?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/_QeRHTuZsCM/index.html</link><description>Today we can tell the remarkable story of Shazia Ramzan, a 15-year-old Pakistani schoolgirl.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/_QeRHTuZsCM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jul 2013 08:39:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Girls flee war, find ''worse'' in camp</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/8hBoSxxJUKo/index.html</link><description>Feet stumbling in the pitch darkness over the uneven ground we make our way with a group of women to one of the bathrooms in the Zaatari camp.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/8hBoSxxJUKo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 09:04:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Impact Your World: How to help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/CoZx3AnFw-k/index.html</link><description>CNN Films'' "Girl Rising" tells the stories of girls across the globe and the power of education to change the world. Are you inspired to help the cause of girls'' education around the world? You can make an impact in many ways, but by just being aware of the issue, you can spread the word. By acting in your own community, you can make a global difference.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/CoZx3AnFw-k" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2013 08:23:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Families of fallen ''hotshots'' need help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/IUkDUWtb-gQ/index.html</link><description>Nineteen elite firefighters died fighting the Yarnell Hill wildfire last month, and over the past few weeks there has been an outpouring of support for their families. But what happens when the cards, letters and casserole dishes quit coming?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/IUkDUWtb-gQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:10:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>When cooking can kill</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/fN2gx5LhHVo/index.html</link><description>For nearly half of the world''s population, building and maintaining a fire is a daily -- and often deadly -- chore.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/fN2gx5LhHVo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 17:52:43 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''I''m not a welfare mom, I''m a soldier''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/5y0EdVXFG34/index.html</link><description>Jaspen Boothe is committed to helping out homeless female veterans.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/5y0EdVXFG34" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2013 21:38:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Wildlife''s worst enemy? Us</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/zpVT-QhYVsI/index.html</link><description>Mona Rutger got the call in October: A bald eagle was flopping around on an airport runway after it had been clipped by a private jet. Unfortunately, it''s something she sees all too often.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zpVT-QhYVsI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2013 18:12:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Troubled youth run ''old skool'' bistro</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/QKecr7ib-2w/index.html</link><description>As a juvenile corrections officer in Southern California, Teresa Goines found it rewarding to work with troubled youth and help them turn their lives around.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/QKecr7ib-2w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2013 15:23:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pregnant and homeless: The real cost</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/jP1s9z9CjAg/index.html</link><description>Martha Ryan couldn''t believe it. She had never heard of women who were pregnant and homeless. But in one night, she met three.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/jP1s9z9CjAg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 May 2013 15:59:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Death toll rises in China landslide</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/asia/china-landslide/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/8kqO7buCLpo/index.html</link><description>Rescuers in China had pulled a total of 31 bodies from the wreckage from a landslide the size of a small town that rushed down a mountain earlier in the week.\r\nState-run CCTV reported on Friday that the number of people missing in and around the city of Dujiangyan was 166, up from 107 the previous day.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/8kqO7buCLpo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 14:26:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/asia/china-landslide/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Keeping chivalry alive in India</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/india-males-violence/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/x0VQ78_V908/index.html</link><description>Many female travelers are scrubbing India off their destination lists after the horrific gang rape and murder of a Delhi student in December 2012.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/x0VQ78_V908" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:09:28 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/india-males-violence/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Buddhists convicted of massacre</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/myanmar-buddhist-conviction-muslim-massacre/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Gl3WLGMMYf4/index.html</link><description>Myanmar''s courts convicted 22 Buddhists this week for sparking anti-Muslim violence and bloodshed in March, according to a state-run newspaper.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Gl3WLGMMYf4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:04:26 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/myanmar-buddhist-conviction-muslim-massacre/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Your solstice traditions </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/20/world/strange-silly-summer-traditions/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/h0Kk48INMX0/index.html</link><description>If Stonehenge is anything to go by, summer celebrations have a millennia-old history. While the ancient druids may have commemorated the fertility of the season, many of us are just happy to get outdoors.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/h0Kk48INMX0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2013 06:35:52 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/20/world/strange-silly-summer-traditions/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Summer solstice: It''s all about sex</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/summer-solstice-world-celebrations-sex/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/q4DRiuXo06w/index.html</link><description>In the Northern Hemisphere, the summer solstice has a history of stirring libidos, and it''s no wonder. The longest day of the year tends to kick off the start of the summer season, and with it, the harvest. It should then come as no surprise that the solstice is linked to fertility -- both of the vegetal and human variety.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/q4DRiuXo06w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 05:06:31 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/summer-solstice-world-celebrations-sex/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Your most memorable moments</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2012/12/20/world/your-best-moment-2012/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/9BHrf62Mb9E/index.html</link><description>For some it was an exhilarating holiday to an exotic place, finding new love or conquering their greatest fear. For others, it was witnessing an historic event.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/9BHrf62Mb9E" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 05:10:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2012/12/20/world/your-best-moment-2012/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Why bin Laden wore a cowboy hat</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/asia/pakistan-bin-laden-report/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/t8aQKVUBmAc/index.html</link><description>Osama bin Laden typically wore a cowboy hat while tending his garden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/t8aQKVUBmAc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jul 2013 08:37:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/asia/pakistan-bin-laden-report/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>The world''s other Malalas</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/gallery/malala-is-not-alone/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Zm2GhvYFaq0/index.html</link><description>As Malala Yousafzai, the Pakistani schoolgirl shot by the Taliban for campaigning for girls'' education, prepares to lead the first ever youth takeover of the United Nations General Assembly on Friday, we meet five other female campaigners around the world. These are all inspirational young women who have overcome poverty and hardship and are passionate about giving something back to their communities.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Zm2GhvYFaq0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:50:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/gallery/malala-is-not-alone/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Landslide ravages Chinese city</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/11/vo-china-landslide.cctv.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/ZleCQwXBO9I/vo-china-landslide.cctv.html</link><description>A deadly rain-triggered landslide leaves hundreds displaced in Dujiangyan, China.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/ZleCQwXBO9I" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 11:45:19 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/11/vo-china-landslide.cctv.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>By the Numbers: Royal births</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/by-the-numbers-royal-births/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/8mEoMRctkB8/index.html</link><description>Prince William and his wife, Catherine, the Duchess of Cambridge, are expecting their first baby this month.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/8mEoMRctkB8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 12:27:32 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/by-the-numbers-royal-births/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Teens'' killings ignite Egypt anger</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/09/intl-egypt-violence-outrage-wedeman-pkg.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/vvD0wBQqVbM/intl-egypt-violence-outrage-wedeman-pkg.cnn.html</link><description>Grisly killings in Alexandria are shedding an unflattering light on Egypt''s jihadists. CNN''s Ben Wedeman reports.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/vvD0wBQqVbM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 11:46:27 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/09/intl-egypt-violence-outrage-wedeman-pkg.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>DSK still upset over ''perp walk''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/europe/france-dsk/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/C1vIDOHP-Po/index.html</link><description>The former chief of the International Monetary Fund who resigned after being charged two years ago with sexually assaulting a maid in a New York city hotel lashed out Tuesday at his treatment by police -- particularly his forced participation in "the perp walk."&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/C1vIDOHP-Po" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 11:46:37 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/europe/france-dsk/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Growing up in an Indian brothel</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/06/world/asia/from-brothel-to-college/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/D_HiErSY0lM/index.html</link><description>Shweta Katti grew up in Mumbai''s red-light district, surrounded by the sex industry. But now her future is bright.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/D_HiErSY0lM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2013 09:17:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/06/world/asia/from-brothel-to-college/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>China''s sex-change pioneer</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/china-jin-xing-sex-change/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/ocEzh-1RC5w/index.html</link><description>Few people have had so much impact on the Chinese attitude towards sexuality and gender equality than Jin Xing.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/ocEzh-1RC5w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 09:38:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/asia/china-jin-xing-sex-change/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Thrill-seekers run with bulls</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/07/running-of-the-bulls.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/iT6_Yp0UPB0/running-of-the-bulls.cnn.html</link><description>Thrill-seekers tested their bravery by running alongside fighting bulls through the streets of the Pamplona on Sunday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/iT6_Yp0UPB0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2013 09:11:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/07/running-of-the-bulls.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What happened to Malala''s friend?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/_QeRHTuZsCM/index.html</link><description>Today we can tell the remarkable story of Shazia Ramzan, a 15-year-old Pakistani schoolgirl.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/_QeRHTuZsCM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jul 2013 11:37:55 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pope''s first trip shuns pageantry</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/08/nr-nadeau-italy-pope-visits-lampedusa-refugees.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/tUORfxIby54/nr-nadeau-italy-pope-visits-lampedusa-refugees.cnn.html</link><description>For his first pastoral visit outside Rome, Pope Francis shuns protocol and politics by visiting tiny island of Lampedusa.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/tUORfxIby54" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2013 11:07:25 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/08/nr-nadeau-italy-pope-visits-lampedusa-refugees.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Whale wallops Aussie surfer</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/08/dnt-australia-surfer-knocked-out-by-whale.seven-network.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/P0IMXJI2iGw/dnt-australia-surfer-knocked-out-by-whale.seven-network.html</link><description>A curious surfer only just survived a close encounter with a whale, as a once-in-a-lifetime paddle almost ended in death&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/P0IMXJI2iGw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2013 09:11:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/08/dnt-australia-surfer-knocked-out-by-whale.seven-network.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Feng shui master jailed over will</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/asia/hong-kong-wang/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/OSt5cAw2Ia4/index.html</link><description>The former lover and feng shui master to one of Asia''s wealthiest women has been sentenced to 12 years in jail after being found guilty of forging a will that made him the beneficiary of her multi-billion-dollar fortune following a long-running case that transfixed Hong Kong.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/OSt5cAw2Ia4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 07 Jul 2013 12:14:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/asia/hong-kong-wang/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Spy microphone recordings?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/03/world/europe/uk-ecuador-embassy-microphone/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/TnSKNPrZpNw/index.html</link><description>Ecuador is calling for British authorities to help investigate after officials found a secret recording device planted inside the South American country''s embassy in London.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/TnSKNPrZpNw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 07 Jul 2013 12:13:51 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/03/world/europe/uk-ecuador-embassy-microphone/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>U.S. man in N. Korea: Please help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/03/world/asia/kenneth-bae-korea-interview/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/oor6-3q40qk/index.html</link><description>The American citizen sentenced to 15 years in a North Korean labor camp, has appealed to the Korean authorities for forgiveness and asked the United States for help in securing his release in an exclusive interview from prison obtained Wednesday by CNN.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/oor6-3q40qk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jul 2013 08:38:47 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/03/world/asia/kenneth-bae-korea-interview/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New law: Visit parents or else</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/02/world/asia/china-elderly-law/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/C6FBRMjPYW8/index.html</link><description>Lola Wang, a 28-year-old marketing officer in Shanghai, makes a six-hour trip to Shandong to see her parents twice a year -- once during the Lunar New Year and again during the National Day holiday in October.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/C6FBRMjPYW8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 09:46:56 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/02/world/asia/china-elderly-law/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Green blob covers Chinese waters</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/asia/china-algae-green-blob/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Z4zOixEQcC4/index.html</link><description>For years, China has talked about promoting "green growth." But this probably isn''t what they had in mind.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Z4zOixEQcC4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 08:54:45 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/asia/china-algae-green-blob/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Taliban ''failed,'' Malala says at U.N.</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/united-nations-malala/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/nxeqeVJjDRA/index.html</link><description>Malala Yousafzai, the Pakistani schoolgirl who was shot by the Taliban last year for her efforts to promote girls education, spoke at the United Nations on Friday, her 16th birthday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/nxeqeVJjDRA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 13:18:52 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/united-nations-malala/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Going to school, instead of work</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/05/15/girl-rising-purnima-nepal.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/mK1BlIGo_4Y/girl-rising-purnima-nepal.cnn.html</link><description>A Nepalese girl has her sights on a medical career because of her mother''s blindness. CNN''s Fredricka Whitfield reports.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/mK1BlIGo_4Y" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 29 May 2013 07:01:58 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/05/15/girl-rising-purnima-nepal.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Girls, it''s time to power the world</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/world/amanpour-girl-rising/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/mug9FDJedrI/index.html</link><description>Dear Girls of the World,&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/mug9FDJedrI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 May 2013 10:00:29 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/world/amanpour-girl-rising/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Things I wish I''d known at 15</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2012/10/11/world/gallery/international-day-of-the-girl/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/6QeU-4D4dU4/index.html</link><description>International day of the girl: ''To my 15-year-old self''&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/6QeU-4D4dU4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 May 2013 06:38:35 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2012/10/11/world/gallery/international-day-of-the-girl/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Egypt''s ''revolution of the mind''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/4dAeqTh63YQ/index.html</link><description>The uprising that banished Hosni Mubarak two years ago unleashed a passion in Egypt that shows no sign of diminishing. It also changed the way many Egyptians view their government, says CNN''s Ben Wedeman.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/4dAeqTh63YQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:17:46 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Is Snowden worth the risk?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/latin-america-snowden-asylum/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dWT35VJRmVQ/index.html</link><description>It''s been days since three Latin American presidents offered to give Edward Snowden a safe place to hide out from U.S. authorities. So what''s the holdup? Here are the pros and cons facing leaders in five countries.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dWT35VJRmVQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:45:57 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/latin-america-snowden-asylum/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Blue planet rains liquid glass</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/MJFRh3eVk9M/index.html</link><description>Astronomers have found a deep azure blue planet orbiting another star 63 light years away -- the first time they''ve been able to determine the actual color of a planet outside our solar system, NASA and the European Space Agency said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/MJFRh3eVk9M" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:07:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mapping a mountain with Google</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/12/lklv-magnay-japan-fuji.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/iqH-Hu6-Xzc/lklv-magnay-japan-fuji.cnn.html</link><description>Google teams go back up Mt. Fuji, taking their high tech backpacks up to the top of the Japan''s tallest volcano.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/iqH-Hu6-Xzc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:53:10 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/12/lklv-magnay-japan-fuji.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Odds of a Snowden getaway?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/us/snowden-getaway-options/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/lx9vBPvuvys/index.html</link><description>Will Edward Snowden get away? Yes and no. Understanding this contradiction involves looking at what both the government and Snowden have in their favor.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/lx9vBPvuvys" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 14:17:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/us/snowden-getaway-options/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Egypt''s ''revolution of the mind''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/4dAeqTh63YQ/index.html</link><description>The uprising that banished Hosni Mubarak two years ago unleashed a passion in Egypt that shows no sign of diminishing. It also changed the way many Egyptians view their government, says CNN''s Ben Wedeman.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/4dAeqTh63YQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:17:46 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Girls defy Taliban in Pakistan</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/12/pkg-mohsin-pakistan-swat-girls-school.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/pIqn3MylqkM/pkg-mohsin-pakistan-swat-girls-school.cnn.html</link><description>Saima Mohsin travels to Swat, where Malala Yousafzai was shot by the Taliban. She visits an all-female college.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/pIqn3MylqkM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:58:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/12/pkg-mohsin-pakistan-swat-girls-school.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>The world''s other Malalas</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/gallery/malala-is-not-alone/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Zm2GhvYFaq0/index.html</link><description>As Malala Yousafzai, the Pakistani schoolgirl shot by the Taliban for campaigning for girls'' education, prepares to lead the first ever youth takeover of the United Nations General Assembly on Friday, we meet five other female campaigners around the world. These are all inspirational young women who have overcome poverty and hardship and are passionate about giving something back to their communities.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Zm2GhvYFaq0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 08:16:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/gallery/malala-is-not-alone/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>How bin Laden kept hidden</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/asia/pakistan-bin-laden-report/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/t8aQKVUBmAc/index.html</link><description>Osama bin Laden typically wore a cowboy hat while tending his garden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/t8aQKVUBmAc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:51:26 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/asia/pakistan-bin-laden-report/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>How to nominate a CNN Hero</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/07/cnnheroes-nominate.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/oiqnEs2GWK8/cnnheroes-nominate.cnn.html</link><description>A CNN Hero''s journey to global recognition begins with a nomination by someone who''s been touched by their efforts.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/oiqnEs2GWK8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2013 07:07:51 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/07/cnnheroes-nominate.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Last year''s top ten</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/20/world/gallery/cnn-heroes-2012/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/d2vE1rCKrps/index.html</link><description>The top 10 Heroes: In their own words&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/d2vE1rCKrps" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2013 07:13:58 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/20/world/gallery/cnn-heroes-2012/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Snowden seeks temporary asylum in Russia</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/russia-us-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/NrQG1uxDABo/index.html</link><description>American intelligence leaker Edward Snowden is due to hold a meeting with human rights groups Friday, the press service for Moscow''s Sheremetyevo International Airport said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/NrQG1uxDABo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:32:45 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/russia-us-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Six dead in train derailment near Paris</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/ey-cBfexrAk/index.html</link><description>French police say at least eight people were killed in a train derailment in Bretigny sur Orge, about 15 miles south of Paris, according to CNN affiliate BFMTV.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/ey-cBfexrAk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 17:01:11 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>U.S. State Department calls for Morsy''s release</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.co