6lg/story01.htm</link><description>PARIS (Reuters) - Syria''s opposition coalition wants to create a 10-person executive council to reorganize disparate rebel factions into a structured army with adequate financing and weapons, one of its senior members said on Monday.&lt;img width=''1'' height=''1'' src=''http://reuters.us.feedsportal.com/c/35217/f/654198/s/2eb1305e/mf.gif'' border=''0''/&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;\r\n&lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=-tnlg2vs6lg:M5ZNXwVUl3U:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=-tnlg2vs6lg:M5ZNXwVUl3U:F7zBnMyn0Lo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=-tnlg2vs6lg:M5ZNXwVUl3U:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=-tnlg2vs6lg:M5ZNXwVUl3U:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=-tnlg2vs6lg:M5ZNXwVUl3U:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Reuters/worldNews/~4/-tnlg2vs6lg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><category domain="">worldNews</category><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 17:39:50 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/07/15/us-syria-crisis-opposition-idUSBRE96E0OP20130715?feedType=RSS&amp;feedName=worldNews</guid><feedburner:origLink>http://reuters.us.feedsportal.com/c/35217/f/654198/s/2eb1305e/l/0L0Sreuters0N0Carticle0C20A130C0A70C150Cus0Esyria0Ecrisis0Eopposition0EidUSBRE96E0AOP20A130A7150DfeedType0FRSS0GfeedName0FworldNews/story01.htm</feedburner:origLink></item><item><title>Myanmar President pledges prisoner release, peace</title><link>http://feeds.reuters.com/~r/Reuters/worldNews/~3/_Svr2OVUTXE/story01.htm</link><description>LONDON (Reuters) - The president of Myanmar promised to release all pol