.cnn.com/2013/07/15/sport/remembering-andrew-simpson/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/Ot-qf5rZ5eM/index.html</link><description>On May 9, an accident ahead of the America''s Cup brought a glittering sailing career to a premature end.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/Ot-qf5rZ5eM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 12:48:43 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/sport/remembering-andrew-simpson/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Woman gored in Spain''s bull-run finale</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/travel/running-of-the-bulls-finale/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/hErAxa7qODc/index.html</link><description>Running of the Bulls ends with third consecutive day of serious injuries&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/hErAxa7qODc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 21:09:31 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/travel/running-of-the-bulls-finale/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Italian senator compares black politician to orangutan</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/italy-politics-racism/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/vNSCeMV94wY/index.html</link><description>The United States isn''t the only Western country dealing with racial tension. Racism is alive and well in Europe, as shown by an ugly, explosive remark at a high political level in Italy that surfaced this weekend.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/vNSCeMV94wY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 21:09:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/italy-politics-racism/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Woman dies during English Channel charity swim</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/channel-swimmer-death/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/rCuUqK7DX1A/index.html</link><description>A British woman on a charity swim across the English Channel died during her bid, according to a post on her fundraising Facebook page.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/rCuUqK7DX1A" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 12:40:23 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/channel-swimmer-death/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>French rail chief blames deadly derailment on faulty part</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/wZ6D0hg9JLg/index.html</link><description>At least six people were killed and 22 injured in a train derailment on Friday just south of Paris, French President Francois Hollande said. The cause of train''s derailment remains unknown.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/wZ6D0hg9JLg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 21:10:35 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Merkel wants EU data protection pact</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/14/business/merkel-eu-data-protection/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/25v31kixHig/index.html</link><description>Angela Merkel, the German chancellor, has called for a strict European agreement on data protection requiring all internet service providers to reveal what personal information they have stored, and to whom they have made it available.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/25v31kixHig" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2013 23:49:43 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/14/business/merkel-eu-data-protection/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Extra police sent to Northern Ireland after riots</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/northern-ireland-unrest/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/D_xdp4vyppI/index.html</link><description>Hundreds of additional police officers are being sent from Britain to Northern Ireland on Saturday after a night of loyalist rioting in Belfast left 32 officers injured across the city, police said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/D_xdp4vyppI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2013 23:07:10 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/northern-ireland-unrest/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Bus, truck crash in Moscow, kills 18</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/russia-bus-crash/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/p9z6n7RNqto/index.html</link><description>A crash involving a bus carrying children and a large truck killed 14 people in a Moscow suburb Saturday, authorities said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/p9z6n7RNqto" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2013 23:06:23 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/russia-bus-crash/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mercedes used by Fangio sells for nearly $30 million </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/13/sport/motorsport/formula-one-car-auction/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/oWPhi1BmEGg/index.html</link><description>A