~r/rss/edition_world/~4/DIN-J-K6Lr8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 15:12:19 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/italy-politics-racism/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>French rail chief blames derailment on faulty part</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Du83Cb5qVrs/index.html</link><description>A fatal train derailment south of Paris was caused by a part disconnecting from the switching mechanism on the tracks, the head of the French national railway company said Saturday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Du83Cb5qVrs" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 13:09:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/france-train-derailment/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Dementia village'' inspires new care</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Eg-e8KNd3MM/index.html</link><description>A cutting edge dementia facility -- where residents can do anything except leave and where their every move is watched by carers who also staff the village shops -- is offering a new way to deal with long term care.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Eg-e8KNd3MM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:15:02 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Saudi Arabia warns pilgrims to wear masks</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/meast/saudi-arabia-pilgrims-masks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/T-iwKpFUJKY/index.html</link><description>Saudi Arabia is asking pilgrims to cover their mouths with a mask while in crowded places -- or risk spreading a deadly disease.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/T-iwKpFUJKY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 08:28:46 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/meast/saudi-arabia-pilgrims-masks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Police hurt in Belfast riots</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/northern-ireland-unrest/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/GyW0s1s-tOg/index.html</link><description>Hundreds of additional police officers are being sent from Britain to Northern Ireland on Saturday after a night of loyalist rioting in Belfast left 32 officers injured across the city, police said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/GyW0s1s-tOg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:18:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/europe/northern-ireland-unrest/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>DSK: I have no problem with women</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/france-dsk/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/c4i_HQXvGUY/index.html</link><description>Despite his brushes with the law involving allegations of sexual assault and prostitution, Dominique Strauss-Kahn insisted in a CNN interview that he doesn''t "have any kind of problem with women."&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/c4i_HQXvGUY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:04:56 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/france-dsk/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pope lays down law on child abuse</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/vatican-child-abuse/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/pZZ_mCJfOUY/index.html</link><description>Pope Francis has laid down a law making it a crime to abuse children sexually or physically on Vatican grounds, the Holy See announced Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/pZZ_mCJfOUY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:01:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/vatican-child-abuse/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>WikiLeaks hints at Snowden ''flight''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/americas/nsa-snowden-venezuela/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/nbAJ_9-j7GQ/index.html</link><description>As speculation grows over Edward Snowden''s path to freedom, WikiLeaks teased that his "flight of liberty" campaign starts Wednesday, promising further details.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/nbAJ_9-j7GQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 08:51:23 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/americas/nsa-snowden-venezuela/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Raped girl stirs Chile abortion debate</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/1qeHYyjRlfM/index.html</link><description>Chilean President Sebastian Pinera stoked an abortion debate in his country over remarks he made about an 11-year-old girl who became pregnant after being raped by her stepfather.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/1qeHYyjRlfM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:02:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Soccer referee dismembered</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/07/world/americas/brazil-soccer-dismemberment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/xul5046QnVc/index.html</link><description>The argument started over a red card.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/xul5046QnVc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:46:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/07/world/americas/brazil-soccer-dismemberment/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Car bomb rips through Beirut</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/meast/lebanon-blast/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/WXTjXBTJwQQ/index.html</link><description>A large explosion rocked southern Beirut on Tuesday, unleashing an inferno in the Bir El Abed neighborhood, Lebanon''s National News Agency reported.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/WXTjXBTJwQQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:43:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/meast/lebanon-blast/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Attack kills 33 in Iraq cafe</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/meast/iraq-suicide-bomber/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/uMmBAEqTCE0/index.html</link><description>At least 33 people were killed and 26 others hurt on Friday night when a suicide bomber with an explosive vest blew himself up inside an coffee shop where patrons were playing a popular Ramadan game in Kirkuk, Iraq, police said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/uMmBAEqTCE0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:17:55 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/meast/iraq-suicide-bomber/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Freerunners'' find feet in Baghdad</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/02/world/meast/iraq-parkour-freerunning/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/uThL4SXIZ7k/index.html</link><description>Leaping from rooftops and doing backflips off walls is when Prince Haydar feels the most free.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/uThL4SXIZ7k" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jul 2013 08:49:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/02/world/meast/iraq-parkour-freerunning/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Boxing gives teenagers hope </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/africa/fight-club-boxing-johannesburg/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/hCvfRWZjF7U/index.html</link><description>Her gloves held high, Rita Mrwebi dances in the middle of a blue boxing ring. Eyes focused straight ahead, she unleashes a flurry of thudding jabs and powerful hooks.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/hCvfRWZjF7U" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:19:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/africa/fight-club-boxing-johannesburg/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mbeki: Mandela will pull through</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/africa/south-africa-mandela-mbeki/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/sc-xAQr-YX0/index.html</link><description>Thabo Mbeki, who succeeded Nelson Mandela as South Africa''s 14 years ago, says the ailing revered statesmen will pull through.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/sc-xAQr-YX0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15