st movie puppets</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/showbiz/10-greatest-movie-puppets/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/z5MBB2hnTx0/index.html</link><description>Another year, another summer movie schedule overflowing with big-budget CGI blockbusters.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/z5MBB2hnTx0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 04:33:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/showbiz/10-greatest-movie-puppets/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''War Horse'' puppet comes to life</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/04/aom-puppetry-war-horse.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/k9BDXvfwmgM/aom-puppetry-war-horse.cnn.html</link><description>Nick Glass speaks to the puppeteers behind the stage hit "War Horse" to find out how they bring its equine star to life.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/k9BDXvfwmgM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 04:33:34 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/04/aom-puppetry-war-horse.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Basil Twist: Puppetry in motion</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/living/2013/06/24/aom-glass-basil-twist.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/EpZRM-QwZXU/aom-glass-basil-twist.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Nick Glass explores the art and innovation behind performing with puppets, with master puppeteer Basil Twist.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/EpZRM-QwZXU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jul 2013 12:11:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/living/2013/06/24/aom-glass-basil-twist.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Media in royal baby frenzy</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/11/ctw-royal-baby-media-frenzy.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/f8GcVlz6u5s/ctw-royal-baby-media-frenzy.cnn.html</link><description>Becky Anderson takes us behind the scenes to show us what to expect after the birth announcement of a royal baby.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/f8GcVlz6u5s" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 09:07:08 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/11/ctw-royal-baby-media-frenzy.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Dementia village'' provides care</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/XD0WvdUdRCU/index.html</link><description>A cutting edge dementia facility -- where residents can do anything except leave and where their every move is watched by carers who also staff the village shops -- is offering a new way to deal with long term care.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/XD0WvdUdRCU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 21:57:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New planet that rains glass</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/o7JqcMvJHW0/index.html</link><description>Astronomers have found a deep azure blue planet orbiting another star 63 light years away -- the first time they''ve been able to determine the actual color of a planet outside our solar system, NASA and the European Space Agency said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/o7JqcMvJHW0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 02:32:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Is anyone listening to angry DSK?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/dsk-poirier/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/92wo4y65ZPM/index.html</link><description>It may feel to us, in France, as if Dominique Strauss-Kahn has constantly been in the news since that fateful afternoon of May 14, 2011, when NYPD officers arrested him on board an Air France flight bound to Berlin. The then-head of the International Monetary Fund was due to meet German Chancellor Angela Merkel to try to solve the euro crisis.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/92wo4y65ZPM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 14:21:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/dsk-poirier/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mr. Putin, lift ban on adoptions</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/bachmann-adoption-russia/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/AZfQT7bD3Ww/index.html</link><description>Michele Bachmann says President Vladimir Putin should consider lifting the ban on American adoptions of Russian orphans.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/AZfQT7bD3Ww" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 13:02:09 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/bachmann-adoption-russia/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Tracking Snowden across globe</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/snowden-global-map/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/hN-4PSbWQHE/index.html</link><description>&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/hN-4PSbWQHE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 11:28:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/snowden-global-map/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>By the Numbers: Royal births</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/by-the-numbers-royal-births/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/YlCHsGxrLlE/index.html</link><description>Prince William and his wife, Catherine, the Duchess of Cambridge, are expecting their first baby this month.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/YlCHsGxrLlE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 12:19:37 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/by-the-numbers-royal-births/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>How we''ll know of the royal birth</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/royal-baby-qa/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/R9fKWVOesfk/index.html</link><description>Any day now, the Duchess of Cambridge is due to give birth to her first baby. What will happen once it arrives?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/R9fKWVOesfk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 12:21:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/world/europe/royal-baby-qa/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Living in an underwater village</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/tech/cousteau-why-im-going-to-live-in-an-underwater-village/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/7S9mRKujaik/index.html</link><description>Legendary diver Jacques Cousteau''s grandson, Fabien, will live in an underwater laboratory, 20 meters below the surface of the ocean, for an unprecedented 31 days.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/7S9mRKujaik" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:37:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/tech/cousteau-why-im-going-to-live-in-an-underwater-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Thrill of Pamplona bull runners</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/travel/la-pamplona/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/BBUq0996AAU/index.html</link><description>More and more people risk injury each year at thrilling symbol of Spanish culture.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/BBUq0996AAU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jul 2013 07:50:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/travel/la-pamplona/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What''s in a royal name?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/europe/britain-royal-baby-name/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/5HMoOjw5KVk/index.html</link><description>Way back in the mists of time, when schoolkids were expected to learn seemingly endless lists of facts off by heart, they chanted a poem to remember the names of England''s kings and queens.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/5HMoOjw5KVk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 07:00:02 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/05/world/europe/britain-royal-baby-name/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Putin: Snowden is ''shifting position'' </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/russia-putin-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/PSxVBf2qVMU/index.html</link><description>Russian President Vladimir Putin says U.S. intelligence leaker Edward Snowden appears to be "shifting his position somewhat" on asylum, state-run media said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/PSxVBf2qVMU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 21:11:20 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/russia-putin-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Rowling''s secret novel revealed</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/rowling-secret-book/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/F5hFCihfu3E/index.html</link><description>"Harry Potter" creator J.K. Rowling donned an invisibility cloak of her own for her new novel.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/F5hFCihfu3E" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 19:02:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/rowling-secret-book/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Snowden''s transit zone mysteries</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-snowden-goodman-transit/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/9W6qplys2Q8/index.html</link><description>It seemed like an exciting assignment -- go to Moscow on the trail of former NSA contractor Edward Snowden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/9W6qplys2Q8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 13:48:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/russia-snowden-goodman-transit/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Sailing legend ''Bart'' Simpson</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition