tion''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/russia-putin-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/4Pa8P9Dv4II/index.html</link><description>Russian President Vladimir Putin said Monday that American intelligence leaker Edward Snowden appears to be "shifting his position somewhat" when it comes to meeting Russia''s conditions for asylum, according to Russia''s state-run RIA Novosti news agency.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/4Pa8P9Dv4II" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 15:17:10 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/russia-putin-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Woman dies during English Channel charity swim</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/channel-swimmer-death/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/Yv6YpqlhRUo/index.html</link><description>A British woman on a charity swim across the English Channel died during her bid, according to a post on her fundraising Facebook page.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/Yv6YpqlhRUo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 15:07:34 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/europe/channel-swimmer-death/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Egypt swears in interim leaders</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/meast/egypt-government/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/1axRz8zNQ1U/index.html</link><description>Mohamed ElBaradei was sworn in Sunday as Egypt''s interim vice president for foreign relations -- a key step in establishing a temporary government following the recent coup.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/1axRz8zNQ1U" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate