/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/13/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/YPqU6t4HUxo/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</link><description>A dash cam was recording the moment a truck crashed into the side of a bus carrying children in Russia.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/YPqU6t4HUxo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 08:31:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/13/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Egypt''s ''revolution of the mind''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/4dAeqTh63YQ/index.html</link><description>The uprising that banished Hosni Mubarak two years ago unleashed a passion in Egypt that shows no sign of diminishing. It also changed the way many Egyptians view their government, says CNN''s Ben Wedeman.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/4dAeqTh63YQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:17:46 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Is Snowden worth the risk?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/latin-america-snowden-asylum/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dWT35VJRmVQ/index.html</link><description>It''s been days since three Latin American presidents offered to give Edward Snowden a safe place to hide out from U.S. authorities. So what''s the holdup? Here are the pros and cons facing leaders in five countries.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dWT35VJRmVQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:45:57 EDT</