an 260 wounded when Islamist supporters of Mohamed Mursi fought opponents of the deposed Egyptian president and security forces, marking a return of violence that overshadowed the naming of an interim cabinet.&lt;img width=''1'' height=''1'' src=''http://reuters.us.feedsportal.com/c/35217/f/654198/s/2eb40023/mf.gif'' border=''0''/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/165666217697/u/49/f/654198/c/35217/s/2eb40023/a2.htm"&gt;&lt;img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/165666217697/u/49/f/654198/c/35217/s/2eb40023/a2.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/165666217697/u/49/f/654198/c/35217/s/2eb40023/a2t.img" border="0"/&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;\r\n&lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zcV6F3IGgDw:FEWuBtf1N8M:yIl2AUoC8zA"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zcV6F3IGgDw:FEWuBtf1N8M:F7zBnMyn0Lo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=zcV6F3IGgDw:FEWuBtf1N8M:F7zBnMyn0Lo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.reuters.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?a=zcV6F3IGgDw:FEWuBtf1N8M:V_sGLiPBpWU"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Reuters/worldNews?i=zcV6F3IGgDw:FEWuBtf1N8M:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Reuters/worldNews/~4/zcV6F3IGgDw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><category domain="">worldNews</category><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 14:29:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/07/16/us-egypt-protests-idUSBRE96E01E20130716?feedType=RSS&amp;feedName=worldNews</guid><feedburner:origLink>http://reuters.us.feedsportal.com/c/35217/f/654198/s/2eb40023/l/0L0Sreuters0N0Carticle0C20A130C0A70C160Cus0Eegypt0Eprotests0EidUSBRE96E0A1E20A130A7160DfeedType0FRSS0GfeedNam