tion_americas/~4/-D5L3ZGO9uE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 11:06:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/travel/brazil-10-things/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Where could Snowden go? </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/07/02/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/jOBOKEGEV1s/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Tom Foreman looks at the possibilities for NSA leaker Edward Snowden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/jOBOKEGEV1s" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 13:51:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/07/02/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Brazilian football''s spiritual home</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2013/06/28/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/wcQt2mZjO60/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Pedro Pinto tours Brazil''s Maracana Stadium after its costly and problematic redesign for the 2014 World Cup.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/wcQt2mZjO60" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 22:29:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2013/06/28/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Social classes unite in protests</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/28/world/americas/brazil-protests-favelas/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/j6sF5GgmkmA/index.html</link><description>During the past two weeks, millions of Brazilians have taken to the streets to protest years of dissatisfaction and discontent with their government. What started as a student mobilization transformed day by day to incorporate professionals, the middle class, and residents of the favelas, or slums.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/j6sF5GgmkmA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 10:57:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/28/world/americas/brazil-protests-favelas/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ecuador''s poor press freedom</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/27/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Ck049k05SSQ/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</link><description>Ecuador has a poor track record on press freedom, so why would it help Edward Snowden? CNN speaks to a local investigative journalist who blew the whistle in a presidential corruption case.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Ck049k05SSQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 11:07:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/27/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Escape: Best places to hide out</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/26/travel/snowden-places-of-refuge/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/uZ5L0Ab_GKQ/index.html</link><description>Fleeing US law enforcement, the NSA whistleblower Edward Snowden seems stuck for where to go next. CNN Travel''s own top secret document reveals which countries should be on his list ...&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/uZ5L0Ab_GKQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 13:50:51 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/26/travel/snowden-places-of-refuge/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Brazil is thriving, so what gives?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/26/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/kU7Vqp7v_GI/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</link><description>Brazil had finally made it, so why did millions take to the streets? CNN''s Shasta Darlington explains.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/kU7Vqp7v_GI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2013 14:18:10 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/26/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexican eruption caught on tape</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/us/2013/06/18/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/8Io5ks2a8zk/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</link><description>A volcano outside Mexico City erupted Tuesday, sending ash and smoke into the air.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/8Io5ks2a8zk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jun 2013 22:19:08 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/us/2013/06/18/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>A fair World Cup deal for Brazil?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/24/sport/football/brazil-protests-fifa-tax/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/2ZAYhBJuYgo/index.html</link><description>Some of the world''s biggest corporations such as Apple and Google have come under pressure over the way they have saved billions of dollars by exploiting tax loopholes. Now it is the turn of FIFA to defend its lucrative financial arrangements with 2014 World Cup hosts Brazil.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/2ZAYhBJuYgo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Jun 2013 06:01:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/24/sport/football/brazil-protests-fifa-tax/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>A new age of protests?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/19/opinion/ghitis-turkey-protests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/ImCiLBFIuLg/index.html</link><description>Frida Ghitis says in this era of connectivity, a little complaint can erupt into massive demonstrations.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/ImCiLBFIuLg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jun 2013 22:25:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/19/opinion/ghitis-turkey-protests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Man who could have been Pele?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/21/sport/football/heleno-pele-brazil-world-cup-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/JRmUCzyFjDQ/index.html</link><description>Women wanted him. Men wanted to be him.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/JRmUCzyFjDQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2013 10:51:20 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/21/sport/football/heleno-pele-brazil-world-cup-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>A sip of 2.6 billion-year-old water</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/21/world/americas/ancient-water-tasting/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/2cux4G1N8wU/index.html</link><description