('http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_world.rss', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\r\n<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" media="screen" href="/~d/styles/rss2full.xsl"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" media="screen" href="http://rss.cnn.com/~d/styles/itemcontent.css"?><rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:feedburner="http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0" version="2.0">\r\n<channel>\r\n<title>CNN.com - World</title>\r\n<link>http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/index.html?eref=rss_world</link>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n<language>en-US</language>\r\n<copyright>Copyright 2013 Cable News Network LP, LLLP.</copyright>\r\n<pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 18:45:17 EDT</pubDate>\r\n<ttl>10</ttl>\r\n<image>\r\n<title>CNN.com - World</title>\r\n<link>http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/index.html?eref=rss_world</link>\r\n<url>http://i.cdn.turner.com/cnn/.e/img/1.0/logo/cnn.logo.rss.gif</url>\r\n<width>144</width>\r\n<height>33</height>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n</image>\r\n<atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_world" /><feedburner:info uri="rss/edition_world" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><item><title>Malala''s voice stronger, not silenced</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/malala-girls-education/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/zoHCj0KLjRk/index.html</link><description>The attack was meant to silence the outspoken teenager who dared to defy the Taliban''s ban against girls in school. Instead, it only made Malala''s voice more powerful. After a school year that started with a shooting, Malala now eyes a summer of speaking at the U.N., telling her story in a new book and amplifying the issue of girls education.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zoHCj0KLjRk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2013 17:03:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/malala-girls-education/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What happened to Malala''s friend?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/_QeRHTuZsCM/index.html</link><description>Today we can tell the remarkable story of Shazia Ramzan, a 15-year-old Pakistani schoolgirl.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/_QeRHTuZsCM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jul 2013 08:39:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Girls flee war, find ''worse'' in camp</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/8hBoSxxJUKo/index.html</link><description>Feet stumbling in the pitch darkness over the uneven ground we make our way with a group of women to one of the bathrooms in the Zaatari camp.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/8hBoSxxJUKo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 09:04:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Impact Your World: How to help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/CoZx3AnFw-k/index.html</link><description>CNN Films'' "Girl Rising" tells the stories of girls across the globe and the power of education to change the world. Are you inspired to help the cause of girls'' education around the world? You can make an impact in many ways, but by just being aware of the issue, you can spread the word. By acting in your own community, you can make a global difference.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/CoZx3AnFw-k" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2013 08:23:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Families of fallen ''hotshots'' need help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/IUkDUWtb-gQ/index.html</link><description>Nineteen elite firefighters died fighting the Yarnell Hill wildfire last month, and over the past few weeks there has been an outpouring of support for their families. But what happens when the cards, letters and casserole dishes quit coming?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/IUkDUWtb-gQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:10:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>When cooking can kill</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/fN2gx5LhHVo/index.html</link><description>For nearly half of the world''s population, building and maintaining a fire is a daily -- and often deadly -- chore.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/fN2gx5LhHVo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 17:52:43 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''I''m not a welfare mom, I''m a soldier''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/5y0EdVXFG34/index.html</link><description>Jaspen Boothe is committed to helping out homeless female veterans.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/5y0EdVXFG34" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2013 21:38:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Wildlife''s worst enemy? Us</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/zpVT-QhYVsI/index.html</link><description>Mona Rutger got the call in October: A bald eagle was flopping around on an airport runway after it had been clipped by a private jet. Unfortunately, it''s something she sees all too often.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zpVT-QhYVsI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2013 18:12:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Troubled youth run ''old skool'' bistro</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/QKecr7ib-2w/index.html</link><description>As a juvenile corrections officer in Southern California, Teresa Goines found it rewarding to work with troubled youth and help them turn their lives around.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/QKecr7ib-2w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2013 15:23:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pregnant and homeless: The real cost</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/jP1s9z9CjAg/index.html</link><description>Martha Ryan couldn''t believe it. She had never heard of women who were pregnant and homeless. But in one night, she met three.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/jP1s9z9CjAg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 May 2013 15:59:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Protests erupt across Bangladesh</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/bangladesh-verdict-protests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dBfyYLZKx70/index.html</link><description>Protests have erupted across Bangladesh after a tribunal sentenced a former Islamic party leader to 90 years in jail for war crimes.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dBfyYLZKx70" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:55:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/bangladesh-verdict-protests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Philippine rebels agree to deal</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/asia/philippines-rebels-deal/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/yAgxd1PUy7I/index.html</link><description>Muslim rebel leaders in the Philippines'' troubled south will get access to the lion''s share of the region''s natural resources under a new agreement reached in peace talks with the government.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/yAgxd1PUy7I" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:14:31 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/asia/philippines-rebels-deal/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Hundreds escape Indonesian prison</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/indonesia-mass-prison-break/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/EabO-_iOURY/index.html</link><description>Indonesian police are searching for potentially hundreds of escaped inmates following a deadly prison riot in Medan, the capital of the province of North Sumatra. At least five people died, including two guards and three prisoners.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/EabO-_iOURY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:14:45 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/indonesia-mass-prison-break/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>World''s best fireworks displays</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/gallery/celebrates-fortnight-fireworks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/0pcJBg17Qhg/index.html</link><description>From Bastille Day and 4th July to Chinese New Year and Disney Land, your shots of the world''s greatest fireworks.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/0pcJBg17Qhg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 07:48:57 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/gallery/celebrates-fortnight-fireworks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Your solstice traditions </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/20/world/strange-silly-summer-traditions/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/h0Kk48INMX0/index.html</link><description>If Stonehenge is anything to go by, summer celebrations