co</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/world/americas/mexico-immigration-dreamers/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/xLf3i571z8A/index.html</link><description>After awaiting reforms that may or may not come, thousands of young undocumented immigrants have abandoned their American Dream voluntarily or because they were deported. They still consider themselves DREAMers, but now they dream in Mexico.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/xLf3i571z8A" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 13:48:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/world/americas/mexico-immigration-dreamers/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Six Colombians indicted in U.S. agent''s murder</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/justice/virginia-indictment-slain-dea-agent/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Mqlp3JxTKWM/index.html</link><description>A Virginia grand jury indicted six Colombian nationals Thursday for the kidnapping and murder of a Drug Enforcement Administration agent in the South American country during an attempted robbery last month, federal authorities said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Mqlp3JxTKWM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:22:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/justice/virginia-indictment-slain-dea-agent/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ex-CIA chief wanted by Italy arrested in Panama</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-italy-us-rendition/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/TKojwvonNOE/index.html</link><description>One of the 23 Americans whom an Italian court convicted in absentia of kidnapping a terrorism suspect in 2003 has been arrested in Panama on an Italian arrest warrant, the Italian justice ministry''s press office said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/TKojwvonNOE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:21:11 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-italy-us-rendition/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>81 kidnapped migrants rescued in Mexico</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/mexico-migrants-rescued/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/EmslWR3tias/index.html</link><description>A group of 81 migrants held captive in a house in the border city of Reynosa were rescued by Mexican authorities.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/EmslWR3tias" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 10:04:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/mexico-migrants-rescued/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>U.S. hosts Cuba migration talks</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/politics/cuba-migration-talks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/bwa-5Ptd0D4/index.html</link><description>U.S. and Cuban officials held migration talks for the first time in more than two years on Wednesday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/bwa-5Ptd0D4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 01:36:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/politics/cuba-migration-talks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Puerto Rico commits to reform police force</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/justice/puerto-rico-civil-rights/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/mncnRPUTfPw/index.html</link><description>The Justice Department and Puerto Rico signed off on a major civil rights agreement on Wednesday to reform the commonwealth''s very troubled police force.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/mncnRPUTfPw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 22:23:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/justice/puerto-rico-civil-rights/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexico captures major drug lord</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/americas/mexico-zetas-leader-captured/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/rW1ObcSrWAo/index.html</link><description>Mexican authorities have captured the leader of the ruthless Zetas cartel, state media reported Monday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/rW1ObcSrWAo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 00:50:40 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/americas/mexico-zetas-leader-captured/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Raped 11-year-old stirs an abortion debate in Chile</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Iku7FkGuFfI/index.html</link><description>Chilean President Sebastian Pinera stoked an abortion debate in his country over remarks he made about an 11-year-old girl who became pregnant after being raped by her stepfather.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Iku7FkGuFfI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 14:33:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexico takes the cake in overweight list</title><guid isPermaLink="false">