lala now eyes a summer of speaking at the U.N., telling her story in a new book and amplifying the issue of girls education.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zoHCj0KLjRk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 May 2013 17:03:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/malala-girls-education/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>What happened to Malala''s friend?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/_QeRHTuZsCM/index.html</link><description>Today we can tell the remarkable story of Shazia Ramzan, a 15-year-old Pakistani schoolgirl.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/_QeRHTuZsCM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jul 2013 08:39:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/01/opinion/shazia-gordon-brown/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Girls flee war, find ''worse'' in camp</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/8hBoSxxJUKo/index.html</link><description>Feet stumbling in the pitch darkness over the uneven ground we make our way with a group of women to one of the bathrooms in the Zaatari camp.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/8hBoSxxJUKo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 09:04:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/26/world/meast/syria-refugees-child-brides/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Impact Your World: How to help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/CoZx3AnFw-k/index.html</link><description>CNN Films'' "Girl Rising" tells the stories of girls across the globe and the power of education to change the world. Are you inspired to help the cause of girls'' education around the world? You can make an impact in many ways, but by just being aware of the issue, you can spread the word. By acting in your own community, you can make a global difference.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/CoZx3AnFw-k" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2013 08:23:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/04/30/world/iyw-girl-rising/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Families of fallen ''hotshots'' need help</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/IUkDUWtb-gQ/index.html</link><description>Nineteen elite firefighters died fighting the Yarnell Hill wildfire last month, and over the past few weeks there has been an outpouring of support for their families. But what happens when the cards, letters and casserole dishes quit coming?&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/IUkDUWtb-gQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:10:05 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/us/cnnheroes-minor-yarnell-hotshots/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>When cooking can kill</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/fN2gx5LhHVo/index.html</link><description>For nearly half of the world''s population, building and maintaining a fire is a daily -- and often deadly -- chore.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/fN2gx5LhHVo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 17:52:43 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/13/world/americas/cnnheroes-hughes-clean-stove/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''I''m not a welfare mom, I''m a soldier''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/5y0EdVXFG34/index.html</link><description>Jaspen Boothe is committed to helping out homeless female veterans.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/5y0EdVXFG34" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jun 2013 21:38:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/06/us/cnnheroes-boothe-female-veterans/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Wildlife''s worst enemy? Us</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/zpVT-QhYVsI/index.html</link><description>Mona Rutger got the call in October: A bald eagle was flopping around on an airport runway after it had been clipped by a private jet. Unfortunately, it''s something she sees all too often.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/zpVT-QhYVsI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 30 May 2013 18:12:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/30/us/cnnheroes-rutger-wildlife/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Troubled youth run ''old skool'' bistro</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/QKecr7ib-2w/index.html</link><description>As a juvenile corrections officer in Southern California, Teresa Goines found it rewarding to work with troubled youth and help them turn their lives around.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/QKecr7ib-2w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 May 2013 15:23:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/16/us/cnnheroes-goines-old-skool/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pregnant and homeless: The real cost</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/jP1s9z9CjAg/index.html</link><description>Martha Ryan couldn''t believe it. She had never heard of women who were pregnant and homeless. But in one night, she met three.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/jP1s9z9CjAg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 May 2013 15:59:12 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/05/09/health/cnnheroes-ryan-homeless-pregnant/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Russia holding massive war games</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/russia-war-games/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/muJt20PDsz8/index.html</link><description>Russia is in the midst of its biggest war games since Soviet times, with 160,000 troops, 130 planes, 70 ships and thousands of tanks and armored vehicles participating in the country''s Far East, according to media reports.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/muJt20PDsz8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 09:26:19 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/russia-war-games/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Blind girl reads Braille with lips</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/asia/hong-kong-blind-student-braille-lips/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/BDNNFVLut1U/index.html</link><description>Tsang Tsz-Kwan may look like an average student in Hong Kong with her standard-issue blue shift dress with a Chinese collar and sensible black shoes. But her ordinary appearance and shy manner mask a steely determination to triumph over tremendous odds.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/BDNNFVLut1U" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 09:26:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/asia/hong-kong-blind-student-braille-lips/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Protests erupt across Bangladesh</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/bangladesh-verdict-protests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dBfyYLZKx70/index.html</link><description>Protests have erupted across Bangladesh after a tribunal sentenced a former Islamic party leader to 90 years in jail for war crimes.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dBfyYLZKx70" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:55:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/asia/bangladesh-verdict-protests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>World''s best fireworks displays</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/gallery/celebrates-fortnight-fireworks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/0pcJBg17Qhg/index.html</link><description>From Bastille Day and 4th July to Chinese New Year and Disney Land, your shots of the world''s greatest fireworks.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/0pcJBg17Qhg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 07:48:57 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/gallery/celebrates-fortnight-fireworks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Your solstice traditions </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/20/world/strange-silly-summer-traditions/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/h0Kk48INMX0/index.html</link><description>If Stonehenge is anything to go by, summer celebrations have a millennia-old history. While the ancient druids may have commemorated the fertility of the season, many of us are just happy to get outdoors.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/h0Kk48INMX0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2013 06:35:52 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/06/20/world/strange-silly-summer-traditions/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Your most memorable moments</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2012/12/20/world/your-best-moment-2012/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/9BHrf62Mb9E/index.html</link><description>For some it was an exhilarating holiday to an exotic place, finding new love or conquering their greatest fear. For others, it was witnessing an historic event.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/9BHrf62Mb9E" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 13 Jun 2013 05:10:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2012/12/20/world/your-best-moment-2012/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Wedeman: What I saw in Egypt</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/17/wedeman-egypt-in-crisis-reflection.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dleiQVnicAQ/wedeman-egypt-in-crisis-reflection.cnn.html</link><description>CNN Senior International Correspondent Ben Wedeman talks about his experiences covering the Egyptian crisis.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dleiQVnicAQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 15:53:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/17/wedeman-egypt-in-crisis-reflection.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New stunt for ''action man'' Putin</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/action-man-russian-president-putin/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/_DpikkqMmMk/index.html</link><description>He''s fired darts at a gray whale, sped through St Petersburg in an F1 car, and taken a supersonic flight in a bomber jet.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/_DpikkqMmMk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:52:26 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/action-man-russian-president-putin/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Town scarred by runaway train</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/americas/canada-train-town-profile/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/bNIBsksxQug/index.html</link><description>After a runaway train tore through the heart of Lac-Megantic, Quebec, the world shuddered as newscasts hammered home the possible cause of death. "It''s like 9/11," one newspaper editor said. "All they find will be ashes."&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/bNIBsksxQug" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 08:16:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/americas/canada-train-town-profile/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Who leaked Rowling pen name?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/16/mclaughlin-rowling-book-leak.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/ECBEP_huNhA/mclaughlin-rowling-book-leak.cnn.html</link><description>J.K. Rowling, the pen name, and the mysterious midnight tweet. CNN''s Erin McLaughlin investigates.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/ECBEP_huNhA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 15:54:39 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/16/mclaughlin-rowling-book-leak.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Taliban ''failed,'' Malala tells U.N.</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/united-nations-malala/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/nxeqeVJjDRA/index.html</link><description>Malala Yousafzai, the Pakistani schoolgirl who was shot by the Taliban last year for her efforts to promote girls education, spoke at the United Nations on Friday, her 16th birthday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/nxeqeVJjDRA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 08:11:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/12/world/united-nations-malala/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Marooned at the world''s end</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/americas/deadly-arctic-expedition/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/GjTiMYW0f4Y/index.html</link><description>Capt. Robert Bartlett was awakened by a sharp crack, like a gunshot. His ship was sinking.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/GjTiMYW0f4Y" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 10:56:29 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/americas/deadly-arctic-expedition/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Stuck woman mistaken for ghost</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/16/early-woman-stuck-between-walls.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/JLgPU4a9X5A/early-woman-stuck-between-walls.cnn.html</link><description>A woman fell through a narrow gap between two walls and homeowners though that her calls for help belonged to a ghost.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/JLgPU4a9X5A" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 09:15:08 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/07/16/early-woman-stuck-between-walls.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Blue planet rains liquid glass</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/MJFRh3eVk9M/index.html</link><description>Astronomers have found a deep azure blue planet orbiting another star 63 light years away -- the first time they''ve been able to determine the actual color of a planet outside our solar system, NASA and the European Space Agency said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/MJFRh3eVk9M" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 08:07:15 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Dash cam shows Russia bus crash</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/13/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/YPqU6t4HUxo/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</link><description>A dash cam was recording the moment a truck crashed into the side of a bus carrying children in Russia.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/YPqU6t4HUxo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 08:31:54 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/international/2013/07/13/vo-russia-bus-crash.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Egypt''s ''revolution of the mind''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/4dAeqTh63YQ/index.html</link><description>The uprising that banished Hosni Mubarak two years ago unleashed a passion in Egypt that shows no sign of diminishing. It also changed the way many Egyptians view their government, says CNN''s Ben Wedeman.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/4dAeqTh63YQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 13:17:46 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/meast/egypt-reporter-notebook-wedeman/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Growing up in an Indian brothel</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/06/world/asia/from-brothel-to-college/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/D_HiErSY0lM/index.html</link><description>Shweta Katti grew up in Mumbai''s red-light district, surrounded by the sex industry. But now her future is bright.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/D_HiErSY0lM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2013 09:17:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/06/world/asia/from-brothel-to-college/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Is Snowden worth the risk?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/latin-america-snowden-asylum/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/dWT35VJRmVQ/index.html</link><description>It''s been days since three Latin American presidents offered to give Edward Snowden a safe place to hide out from U.S. authorities. So what''s the holdup? Here are the pros and cons facing leaders in five countries.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/dWT35VJRmVQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 11:45:57 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/latin-america-snowden-asylum/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Why bin Laden wore a cowboy hat</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/asia/pakistan-bin