nt came to swoop in and make an arrest.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/UtSpF93bd3w" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:18:27 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/americas/mexico-zetas-leader-captured/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>North Korea to Panama: Release our ship, crew</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/americas/panama-north-korean-ship/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/urs5CGA4cj0/index.html</link><description>North Korea has a message for Panamanian authorities who seized a cargo ship and arrested its crew: release the ship and let them go.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/urs5CGA4cj0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 19:20:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/americas/panama-north-korean-ship/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Steadily improving'' Mandela turns 95</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/africa/south-africa-mandela/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/uv13oRi-FOE/index.html</link><description>As an ailing Nelson Mandela recuperates in a South African hospital, the world celebrated his 95th birthday Thursday, honoring his legacy in various ways, including performing 67 minutes of community service.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/uv13oRi-FOE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 11:34:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/africa/south-africa-mandela/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Syrian refugees plead with Kerry in Jordan</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/meast/syria-civil-war/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/AqRQUTBrqmo/index.html</link><description>Secretary of State John Kerry got a first-hand look at Syrian suffering Thursday, when he visited a U.N. refugee camp in Jordan.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/AqRQUTBrqmo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:33:26 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/meast/syria-civil-war/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Royal baby overdue</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/uk-royal-baby/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/7DAajBQVN1M/index.html</link><description>Royal watchers eagerly await the arrival of a child that will be heir to the British throne. Here''s what you need to know and the latest developments:&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/7DAajBQVN1M" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:32:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/uk-royal-baby/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Snowden will leave airport in a few days, lawyer says</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/russia-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/pnDlswv-xMo/index.html</link><description>American intelligence leaker Edward Snowden will likely leave the transit zone in a Moscow airport where he''s been holed up for weeks "in the next few days," his lawyer said Wednesday in Russia.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/pnDlswv-xMo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 09:09:39 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/russia-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Outspoken Putin critic sentenced to prison</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/russia-navalny-case/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/lgMFInU_zUQ/index.html</link><description>Alexei Navalny has said all along a court would convict him. Not because he''s guilty, but because it would prevent him from running for mayor of Moscow.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/lgMFInU_zUQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:25:14 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/russia-navalny-case/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>England, Wales set for same-sex marriages in 2014</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-same-sex-marriage/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/6RCX5D1Myeg/index.html</link><description>A bill to allow same-sex marriage in England and Wales is now law, though the unions aren''t expected to take place until 2014.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/6RCX5D1Myeg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:42:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-same-sex-marriage/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Cruise ship captain wants plea deal</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/italy-costa-concordia-trial/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/J0hXaEsx_dM/index.html</link><description>A year and a half after the luxury cruise liner Costa Concordia ran aground off Italy with the loss of 32 lives, the trial of the ship''s captain is due to begin Wednesday in the city of Grosseto.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/J0hXaEsx_dM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:56:18 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/italy-costa-concordia-trial/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Greece to reform civil service</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/greece-civil-service/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/CI_jJxj-qq0/index.html</link><description>The Greek parliament has approved controversial reforms of the civil service and tax administration, opening the way for mass dismissals of state employees in return for a â‚¬6.8bn aid disbursement by international lenders.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/CI_jJxj-qq0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:55:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/greece-civil-service/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Dozens arrested in Istanbul raids</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/europe/turkey-protest-arrests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/qsoDjRQGRzg/index.html</link><description>Turkish counter-terror police launched pre-dawn raids against scores of targets across Turkey''s largest city Tuesday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/qsoDjRQGRzg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 08:58:55 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/europe/turkey-protest-arrests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Death toll rises in train disaster</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/americas/canada-runaway-train/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/nOeUVFXl7zw/index.html</link><description>The death toll grew to 38 on Tuesday as crews recovered three more bodies in last week''s devastating train derailment in the Canadian town of Lac-Megantic, said Genevieve Guilbault, spokeswoman for the Quebec coroner''s office.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/nOeUVFXl7zw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 09:00:11 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/americas/canada-runaway-train/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Raped girl stirs Chile abortion debate</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/1qeHYyjRlfM/index.html</link><description>Chilean President Sebastian Pinera stoked an abortion debate in his country over remarks he made about an 11-year-old girl who became pregnant after being raped by her stepfather.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/1qeHYyjRlfM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:02:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Soccer referee dismembered</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/07/world/americas/brazil-soccer-dismemberment/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/xul5046QnVc/index.html</link><description>The argument started over a red card.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/xul5046QnVc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 08:46:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/07/world/americas/brazil-soccer-dismemberment/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Israel trains for border clash</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/meast/israel-syria-border-war-games/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/tbNDt8QOG40/index.html</link><description>The Israeli army''s Golani brigade recently wrapped up a two-week exercise of ground troops, special forces and air units along Israel''s 81-mile-long (130 km) frontier with Syria. The drill was not aimed at preparing for an all-out war scenario but to respond to a new terror threat that has emerged from the ashes of the Syrian revolution.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/tbNDt8QOG40" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:54:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/meast/israel-syria-border-war-games/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pakistani Taliban arrive in Syria</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/taliban-joining-syrian-fighters/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/i-MSHmEN_q4/index.html</link><description>Taliban fighters from Pakistan have joined forces with al Qaeda forces in Syria to fight Syria''s Bashar al-Assad regime.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/i-MSHmEN_q4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:57:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/taliban-joining-syrian-fighters/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Pilgrims asked to wear masks</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/meast/saudi-arabia-pilgrims-masks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/T-iwKpFUJKY/index.html</link><description>Saudi Arabia is asking pilgrims to cover their mouths with a mask while in crowded places -- or risk spreading a deadly disease.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/T-iwKpFUJKY" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 09:22:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/13/world/meast/saudi-arabia-pilgrims-masks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Euphoria, fear in Egypt</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/africa/egypt-abdelaziz-color/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/ez0NS2z-MgQ/index.html</link><description>Where some see cause to celebrate after President Morsy was removed from power, supporters of the former leader see a coup plot and renewed fears over security.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/ez0NS2z-MgQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 08:57:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/africa/egypt-abdelaziz-color/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Boxing gives teenagers hope </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/africa/fight-club-boxing-johannesburg/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/hCvfRWZjF7U/index.html</link><description>Her gloves held high, Rita Mrwebi dances in the middle of a blue boxing ring. Eyes focused straight ahead, she unleashes a flurry of thudding jabs and powerful hooks.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/hCvfRWZjF7U" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:19:50 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/africa/fight-club-boxing-johannesburg/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mbeki: Mandela will pull through</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/africa/south-africa-mandela-mbeki/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~3/sc-xAQr-YX0/index.html</link><description>Thabo Mbeki, who succeeded Nelson Mandela as South Africa''s 14 years ago, says the ailing revered statesmen will pull through.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_world/~4/sc-xAQr-YX0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2013 11:20:18 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://www.cnn.com/2013/07/14/world/africa/south-africa-mandela-mbeki/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n</channel>\r\n</rss>\r\n', 1374227668);
