long term care.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/XD0WvdUdRCU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 21:57:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/europe/wus-holland-dementia-village/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>New planet that rains glass</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/o7JqcMvJHW0/index.html</link><description>Astronomers have found a deep azure blue planet orbiting another star 63 light years away -- the first time they''ve been able to determine the actual color of a planet outside our solar system, NASA and the European Space Agency said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/o7JqcMvJHW0" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2013 02:32:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/space-blue-planet/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Is anyone listening to angry DSK?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/dsk-poirier/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/92wo4y65ZPM/index.html</link><description>It may feel to us, in France, as if Dominique Strauss-Kahn has constantly been in the news since that fateful afternoon of May 14, 2011, when NYPD officers arrested him on board an Air France flight bound to Berlin. The then-head of the International Monetary Fund was due to meet German Chancellor Angela Merkel to try to solve the euro crisis.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/92wo4y65ZPM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 14:21:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/dsk-poirier/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mr. Putin, lift ban on adoptions</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/bachmann-adoption-russia/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/AZfQT7bD3Ww/index.html</link><description>Michele Bachmann says President Vladimir Putin should consider lifting the ban on American adoptions of Russian orphans.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/AZfQT7bD3Ww" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 13:02:09 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/10/opinion/bachmann-adoption-russia/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Tracking Snowden across globe</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/snowden-global-map/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/hN-4PSbWQHE/index.html</link><description>&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/hN-4PSbWQHE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 11:28:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/09/world/snowden-global-map/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Russia: Navalny freed pending appeal</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/19/world/europe/russia-navalny-case/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/oZC-3BE--fE/index.html</link><description>Russian opposition leader Alexei Navalny was released from detention Friday, one day after a court ordered him to serve five years in prison.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/oZC-3BE--fE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jul 2013 06:38:14 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/19/world/europe/russia-navalny-case/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Royal babies: 5 things to know</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/europe/five-things-to-know-about-royal-baby/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/AD8J42keyjk/index.html</link><description>Think you know all you could ever want to about royal babies amid all the excitement about the new arrival? Well did you know this...&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/AD8J42keyjk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:44:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/europe/five-things-to-know-about-royal-baby/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>''Action man'' Putin in latest stunt</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/action-man-russian-president-putin/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/_V8ELbxpyt8/index.html</link><description>He''s fired darts at a gray whale, sped through St Petersburg in an F1 car, and taken a supersonic flight in a bomber jet.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/_V8ELbxpyt8" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jul 2013 10:24:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/action-man-russian-president-putin/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Murdoch apologizes for criticizing police</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/uk-murdoch-police-probes/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/aZmtI-b8FYM/index.html</link><description>News Corp. Chairman Rupert Murdoch is apologizing for secretly recorded criticism of police investigations into his newspapers, but he says he''s still frustrated by the extent and length of the probes.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/aZmtI-b8FYM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jul 2013 06:14:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/uk-murdoch-police-probes/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>World hopes UK royal baby will be a girl</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/opinion/chernock-royal-baby/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/KE0IGLKYBe4/index.html</link><description>Arianne Chernock explains why popular opinion prefers that the royal couple have a daughter.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/KE0IGLKYBe4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 21:20:07 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/opinion/chernock-royal-baby/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Greeks face new job cuts after austerity vote</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/greece-debt-crisis/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/cGFeflcKHUQ/index.html</link><description>German finance minister Wolfgang Schaeuble is visiting Athens on Thursday for the first time since Greece received its first bailout three years ago, hours after the Greek parliament voted through a bill paving the way for thousands of public sector jobs to be cut.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/cGFeflcKHUQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 06:51:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/europe/greece-debt-crisis/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Lawyer: Snowden to leave Moscow airport soon</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/russia-snowden/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/k8rL1j-Ampo/index.html</link><description>Edward Snowden is likely to leave the transit zone in Moscow''s airport "in the next few days," his lawyer said, after the NSA leaker applied for temporary aslyum in Russia.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/k8rL1j-Ampo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 21:17:59 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/russia-snowden/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>England, Wales set for gay marriages in 2014</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-same-sex-marriage/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/bDqGb6ddd8Y/index.html</link><description>A bill to allow same-sex marriage in England and Wales is now law, though the unions aren''t expected to take place until 2014.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/bDqGb6ddd8Y" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 20:40:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-same-sex-marriage/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Costa Concordia captain on trial over disaster</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/italy-costa-concordia-trial/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/LafoxwC3rVs/index.html</link><description>A year and a half after the luxury cruise liner Costa Concordia ran aground off Italy with the loss of 32 lives, the trial of the ship''s captain is due to begin Wednesday in the city of Grosseto.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/LafoxwC3rVs" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 20:32:33 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/italy-costa-concordia-trial/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Latest developments in the royal baby watch</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-royal-baby/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/j2u-HhF_0iU/index.html</link><description>Royal watchers eagerly await the arrival of a child that will be heir to the British throne. Here''s what you need to know and the latest developments:&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/j2u-HhF_0iU" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 00:41:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/world/europe/uk-royal-baby/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Cycling: French win on Alpe d''Huez</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/sport/cycling-tour-de-france-froome-riblon/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/2E_uOIsE_Rk/index.html</link><description>There was French fever as Christophe Riblon won stage 18 of the Tour de France -- but it was Britain''s Chris Froome who extended his overall lead despite being handed a penalty.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/2E_uOIsE_Rk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 15:20:34 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/sport/cycling-tour-de-france-froome-riblon/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Dutch couple kidnapped in Yemen plead for help in video</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/meast/yemen-dutch-kidnapped/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~3/1798xVurwws/index.html</link><description>A Dutch couple kidnapped in Yemen last month pleaded for help in a video released on Monday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_europe/~4/1798xVurwws" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 00:43:37 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/16/world/meast/yemen-dutch-kidnapped/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n</channel>\r\n</rss>\r\n', 1374236264);
