('http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_americas.rss', '<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\r\n<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" media="screen" href="/~d/styles/rss2full.xsl"?><?xml-stylesheet type="text/css" media="screen" href="http://rss.cnn.com/~d/styles/itemcontent.css"?><rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:feedburner="http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0" version="2.0">\r\n<channel>\r\n<title>CNN.com - Latin America</title>\r\n<link>http://edition.cnn.com/LATINAMERICA/index.html?eref=rss_latinamerica</link>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n<language>en-US</language>\r\n<copyright>Copyright 2013 Cable News Network LP, LLLP.</copyright>\r\n<pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:26:16 EDT</pubDate>\r\n<ttl>10</ttl>\r\n<image>\r\n<title>CNN.com - Latin America</title>\r\n<link>http://edition.cnn.com/LATINAMERICA/index.html?eref=rss_latinamerica</link>\r\n<url>http://i.cdn.turner.com/cnn/.e/img/1.0/logo/cnn.logo.rss.gif</url>\r\n<width>144</width>\r\n<height>33</height>\r\n<description>CNN.com delivers up-to-the-minute news and information on the latest top stories, weather, entertainment, politics and more.</description>\r\n</image>\r\n<atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://rss.cnn.com/rss/edition_americas" /><feedburner:info uri="rss/edition_americas" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><item><title>What to know when visiting Brazil</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/travel/brazil-10-things/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/-D5L3ZGO9uE/index.html</link><description>Brazil might be the biggest country most of the world doesn''t know a whole heckuva a lot about. That''s changing&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/-D5L3ZGO9uE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 11:06:44 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/travel/brazil-10-things/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Where could Snowden go? </title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/07/02/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/jOBOKEGEV1s/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Tom Foreman looks at the possibilities for NSA leaker Edward Snowden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/jOBOKEGEV1s" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 13:51:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/bestoftv/2013/07/02/tsr-foreman-snowdens-asylum-options.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Brazilian football''s spiritual home</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2013/06/28/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/wcQt2mZjO60/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</link><description>CNN''s Pedro Pinto tours Brazil''s Maracana Stadium after its costly and problematic redesign for the 2014 World Cup.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/wcQt2mZjO60" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 30 Jun 2013 22:29:53 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/sports/2013/06/28/pkg-pinto-brazil-maracana-stadium.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Social classes unite in protests</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/28/world/americas/brazil-protests-favelas/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/j6sF5GgmkmA/index.html</link><description>During the past two weeks, millions of Brazilians have taken to the streets to protest years of dissatisfaction and discontent with their government. What started as a student mobilization transformed day by day to incorporate professionals, the middle class, and residents of the favelas, or slums.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/j6sF5GgmkmA" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 10:57:17 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/28/world/americas/brazil-protests-favelas/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ecuador''s poor press freedom</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/27/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Ck049k05SSQ/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</link><description>Ecuador has a poor track record on press freedom, so why would it help Edward Snowden? CNN speaks to a local investigative journalist who blew the whistle in a presidential corruption case.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Ck049k05SSQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 11:07:38 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/27/intl-snowden-why-ecuador-newton-pkg.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Escape: Best places to hide out</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/26/travel/snowden-places-of-refuge/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/uZ5L0Ab_GKQ/index.html</link><description>Fleeing US law enforcement, the NSA whistleblower Edward Snowden seems stuck for where to go next. CNN Travel''s own top secret document reveals which countries should be on his list ...&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/uZ5L0Ab_GKQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jun 2013 13:50:51 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/26/travel/snowden-places-of-refuge/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Brazil is thriving, so what gives?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/26/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/kU7Vqp7v_GI/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</link><description>Brazil had finally made it, so why did millions take to the streets? CNN''s Shasta Darlington explains.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/kU7Vqp7v_GI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 27 Jun 2013 14:18:10 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/world/2013/06/26/pkg-darlington-brazil-awakening.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexican eruption caught on tape</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/us/2013/06/18/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/8Io5ks2a8zk/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</link><description>A volcano outside Mexico City erupted Tuesday, sending ash and smoke into the air.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/8Io5ks2a8zk" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 25 Jun 2013 22:19:08 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/video/data/2.0/video/us/2013/06/18/tsr-snow-mexico-volcano-eruption.cnn.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>A fair World Cup deal for Brazil?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/24/sport/football/brazil-protests-fifa-tax/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/2ZAYhBJuYgo/index.html</link><description>Some of the world''s biggest corporations such as Apple and Google have come under pressure over the way they have saved billions of dollars by exploiting tax loopholes. Now it is the turn of FIFA to defend its lucrative financial arrangements with 2014 World Cup hosts Brazil.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/2ZAYhBJuYgo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 24 Jun 2013 06:01:41 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/24/sport/football/brazil-protests-fifa-tax/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>A new age of protests?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/19/opinion/ghitis-turkey-protests/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/ImCiLBFIuLg/index.html</link><description>Frida Ghitis says in this era of connectivity, a little complaint can erupt into massive demonstrations.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/ImCiLBFIuLg" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jun 2013 22:25:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/19/opinion/ghitis-turkey-protests/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Man who could have been Pele?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/21/sport/football/heleno-pele-brazil-world-cup-football/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/JRmUCzyFjDQ/index.html</link><description>Women wanted him. Men wanted to be him.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/JRmUCzyFjDQ" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 21 Jun 2013 10:51:20 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/06/21/sport/football/heleno-pele-brazil-world-cup-football/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Slow search of N. Korean mystery ship</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-north-korean-ship/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/O0uTGAPKJ5c/index.html</link><description>Since Panamanian authorities discovered undeclared military weapons hidden aboard a North Korean ship, only one of five cargo holds have been unloaded.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/O0uTGAPKJ5c" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:26:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-north-korean-ship/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Blame the U.S. for Mexico obesity?</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/opinion/sutter-mexico-obesity/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/ggS1SygQuyM/index.html</link><description>Experts are putting forward all sorts of reasons Mexico recently became more obese than the United States -- and one of the most overweight countries in the world.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/ggS1SygQuyM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 08:14:47 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/opinion/sutter-mexico-obesity/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Haiti''s ''Garden of Eden''</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/world/americas/urban-oasis-offers-hope-haiti/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/wBi62flPvxo/index.html</link><description>Living amid the garbage-strewn sewage canals, residents of Haiti''s Cite Soleil endure a grim battle for survival every single day. But now, one man is transforming a garbage dump into a vibrant urban garden.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/wBi62flPvxo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 09 Jul 2013 12:47:30 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/world/americas/urban-oasis-offers-hope-haiti/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>The American dream in Mexico</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/world/americas/mexico-immigration-dreamers/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/xLf3i571z8A/index.html</link><description>After awaiting reforms that may or may not come, thousands of young undocumented immigrants have abandoned their American Dream voluntarily or because they were deported. They still consider themselves DREAMers, but now they dream in Mexico.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/xLf3i571z8A" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2013 13:48:36 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/04/world/americas/mexico-immigration-dreamers/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Six Colombians indicted in U.S. agent''s murder</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/justice/virginia-indictment-slain-dea-agent/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Mqlp3JxTKWM/index.html</link><description>A Virginia grand jury indicted six Colombian nationals Thursday for the kidnapping and murder of a Drug Enforcement Administration agent in the South American country during an attempted robbery last month, federal authorities said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Mqlp3JxTKWM" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:22:00 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/justice/virginia-indictment-slain-dea-agent/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Ex-CIA chief wanted by Italy arrested in Panama</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-italy-us-rendition/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/TKojwvonNOE/index.html</link><description>One of the 23 Americans whom an Italian court convicted in absentia of kidnapping a terrorism suspect in 2003 has been arrested in Panama on an Italian arrest warrant, the Italian justice ministry''s press office said Thursday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/TKojwvonNOE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 22:21:11 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/panama-italy-us-rendition/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>81 kidnapped migrants rescued in Mexico</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/mexico-migrants-rescued/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/EmslWR3tias/index.html</link><description>A group of 81 migrants held captive in a house in the border city of Reynosa were rescued by Mexican authorities.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/EmslWR3tias" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 10:04:22 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/world/americas/mexico-migrants-rescued/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>U.S. hosts Cuba migration talks</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/politics/cuba-migration-talks/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/bwa-5Ptd0D4/index.html</link><description>U.S. and Cuban officials held migration talks for the first time in more than two years on Wednesday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/bwa-5Ptd0D4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jul 2013 01:36:49 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/18/politics/cuba-migration-talks/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Puerto Rico commits to reform police force</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/justice/puerto-rico-civil-rights/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/mncnRPUTfPw/index.html</link><description>The Justice Department and Puerto Rico signed off on a major civil rights agreement on Wednesday to reform the commonwealth''s very troubled police force.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/mncnRPUTfPw" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 22:23:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/17/justice/puerto-rico-civil-rights/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexico captures major drug lord</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/americas/mexico-zetas-leader-captured/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/rW1ObcSrWAo/index.html</link><description>Mexican authorities have captured the leader of the ruthless Zetas cartel, state media reported Monday.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/rW1ObcSrWAo" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2013 00:50:40 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/15/world/americas/mexico-zetas-leader-captured/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Raped 11-year-old stirs an abortion debate in Chile</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/Iku7FkGuFfI/index.html</link><description>Chilean President Sebastian Pinera stoked an abortion debate in his country over remarks he made about an 11-year-old girl who became pregnant after being raped by her stepfather.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/Iku7FkGuFfI" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 14:33:48 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/world/americas/chile-abortion-debate/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Mexico takes the cake in overweight list</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/health/us-mexico-obesity/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/RZaOPreUMPc/index.html</link><description>Mexico heads the list of the world''s top industrialized nations. Fat chance you say? Exactly.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/RZaOPreUMPc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Thu, 11 Jul 2013 06:44:01 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/11/health/us-mexico-obesity/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n<item><title>Tropical Storm Chantal fizzles to tropical wave</title><guid isPermaLink="false">http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/world/americas/tropical-weather-chantal/index.html</guid><link>http://rss.cnn.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~3/hDX-TYJ-iB4/index.html</link><description>Tropical Storm Chantal barreled through the Atlantic Ocean early Monday, racing toward the Lesser Antilles, the National Weather Service said.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/rss/edition_americas/~4/hDX-TYJ-iB4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2013 22:09:04 EDT</pubDate><feedburner:origLink>http://edition.cnn.com/2013/07/08/world/americas/tropical-weather-chantal/index.html</feedburner:origLink></item>\r\n</channel>\r\n</rss>\r\n', 1374236266);
